Botulism in blue foxes - Finland: Botulinum toxin type C detected in feed
--------------------------------------------------
As investigated in the Botulinum laboratory at the Department of Food and
Environmental Hygiene, Faculty of Veterinary Medicine, University of
Helsinki, animal feed containing botulinum toxin type C was confirmed to
cause botulism in blue foxes in Finland. Of the so individual raw material
components used for preparing the toxic feed investigated so far, none
contained botulinum toxin. Low numbers of _Clostridium botulinum_ types B
and E cells or spores were detected in individual feed components by a
multiplex PCR assay, but the significance of this finding in the entire
epidemic has not yet been determined.
--
